text: This charming 1, 900 sq. ft. Mid-Century rambler offers the perfect mix of peaceful living and convenience, just minutes from Bellingham and Ferndale. Nestled on a large, sun-filled lot (.25 acre), the home features 3 bedrooms, 1.5 bathrooms, and two living rooms, providing ample space for entertaining or relaxation. A versatile bonus room can serve as a home office or gym, while the dedicated laundry room with a separate entrance adds extra convenience. Step outside to enjoy the covered deck, fully fenced backyard, and two large outbuildings for storage or a workshop. Recent upgrades include a new septic system, heat pump with mini-split for year-round comfort. This is the perfect home for those seeking space, comfort, and a prime location!

Great home in the highly sought after in 55+ age restricted park, Correll Commons. Home has a recently installed walk in shower and is wired for a generator. All appliances stay and it has a full two car garage. This is a stand alone unit with no common walls. This area is centrally located to all local in town Ferndale locations. The park fees include lawn care as well as road maintenance. The community clubhouse features a full kitchen, pool table, guest seating, fireplace and can be reserved for private functions.

Discover the perfect blend of space, tranquility & potential on this serene 5-acre property in a prime mid-county location, just minutes from Bellingham. This mostly flat land offers a peaceful setting with many possibilities. The property features a spacious 1, 040 SF living area above a versatile garage/shop space, complete with 2 bedrooms, 1 bathroom & large covered deck for relaxing or entertaining. With an oversized garage door & tall ceiling there are many great ways to utilize the garage/shop space. 2 power meters already in place on the property. Build your dream home while enjoying the existing shop & living space or keep it as is and embrace the quiet country lifestyle. Dont miss this unique opportunity!

This grand Foursquare Craftsman home is located on a corner lot in the Fountain Village neighborhood zone and was completely redone in 2015! The roof, siding, windows, electrical, plumbing, sheetrock, and all interior was remolded keeping the original character but just updating. The interior doors are all solid wood, 6-panel doors and there are original fir floors on the main level. Bedrooms are upstairs and generously sized with walk-in closets. The kitchen is amazing with cherry shaker-style cabinets and slab granite counters. The laundry/bar area opens to the fully fenced rear yard that mimics the Boundary Bay Beer Garden and is awesome, or you can walk to an abundance of breweries/restaurants and Elizabeth and Broadway parks.

Whether youre looking for a serene retreat or a place to raise animals, this hobby farm on a stunning 4.77-acres has much to offer! This charming 3BR/2BA rambler home offers the perfect blend of comfort and nature. Enjoy easy, one-level living w/ a well-cared-for interior, including hardwood & tile floors throughout, spacious kitchen w/ eating bar & dining room. Large bay windows overlooks woods & creek. Step outside to find a spacious paddock, ideal for horses or other animals, plus a beautiful meadow for grazing. Explore the wooded lands that provide privacy and a peaceful setting, and listen to the gentle sound of the nearby creek. Oversized 2-car garage + shop space, outbuildings & hot tub nestled in the woods makes a serene retreat.

Stunning, one-of-a-kind, shy 7-acre property with a large covered deck that overlooks a private pond & a panorama mountain view. The beautiful log cabin features two bedrooms plus a loft, gorgeous vaulted ceilings, a 2nd deck off the primary bedroom, an updated kitchen and spacious bath, new light fixtures, a new range in '23, & tons of sun pouring in the new Anderson windows. The property features fruit trees, blueberries, currants, a serene willow tree grove, a mature treeline of evergreens for privacy on three sides, & an intimate trail from the southwest end of the circular driveway that leads you through the trees to a workshop, shed, & carport that are on a separate power meter. Only 10 minutes to Lynden & 15-20 minutes to Bellingham.

Welcome to 319 Pacific Hwy, where modern living meets natural beauty. This single-level home, built in 2019, sits on 1.6 acres, surrounded by trees and scenic views. Step inside and experience 1, 568 sqft of open-concept living, featuring 3 bdrms, 2 bthrms, and seamless indoor-outdoor flow w/ both a covered front and back porchideal for year-round enjoyment. The primary suite offers a private retreat with a walk-in closet and an en-suite bathroom. With a fully fenced yard and just a 1/2 mile from Squires Lake Trail and Lake Samish, outdoor adventures are at your doorstep. Plus, enjoy an attached 2-car garage & Xfinity internet. Perfectly positioned on a dead end, between Bellingham and Burlington, you'll enjoy quick and easy access to I-5.
agent: Rachael Wilson, Managing Broker and Realtor

text: This beautiful home has it all! 1, 400+ square feet, 3 bedrooms, 2.5 baths in Creekside Meadows neighborhood.
